<h3>Where to Place Local Keywords</h3>
<p>Local keywords go in specific locations that feed Google Maps rankings:</p>
<ol>
<li><strong>GBP business description</strong> (naturally, not stuffed)</li>
<li><strong>GBP service descriptions</strong> (each service entry)</li>
<li><strong>GBP posts</strong> (weekly updates mentioning your city and services)</li>
<li><strong>Website title tags</strong> (every page should include your city)</li>
<li><strong>Website H1 and H2 headings</strong> (service + location)</li>
<li><strong>Website meta descriptions</strong> (city + service mentions)</li>
<li><strong>Image alt text</strong> (descriptive, including location)</li>
<li><strong><a href="/blog/schema-markup-seo-guide/">Schema markup</a></strong> (LocalBusiness schema with geo coordinates)</li>
</ol>
<h3>Build Location Pages</h3>
<p>If you serve multiple cities or neighborhoods, create a dedicated page for each service area.</p>
<p>A plumber in the Dallas metro should have pages for:</p>
<ul>
<li><code>/plumbing-services-dallas</code></li>
<li><code>/plumbing-services-plano</code></li>
<li><code>/plumbing-services-frisco</code></li>
<li><code>/plumbing-services-fort-worth</code></li>
</ul>
<p>Each page needs unique content. Not the same template with the city name swapped. Google penalizes thin, duplicated location pages. Each page should include:</p>
<ul>
<li>Unique introduction about serving that area</li>
<li>Area-specific testimonials or case studies</li>
<li>Local landmarks or neighborhood references</li>
<li>Unique photos from jobs in that area</li>
<li><a href="/glossary/nap/">NAP information</a> consistent with your GBP</li>
</ul>
<h3>Avoid These Local Keyword Mistakes</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Keyword stuffing your business name.</strong> "Joe's Plumbing | Best Plumber Dallas | Emergency Plumber" violates Google's naming guidelines and risks suspension.</li>
<li><strong>Ignoring "near me" optimization.</strong> You do not target "near me" literally. You optimize for relevance + proximity. Google matches "near me" to the closest relevant businesses.</li>
<li><strong>Targeting only broad terms.</strong> "Plumber" is too competitive. "Emergency plumber for water heater repair" is specific and high-converting.</li>
</ul>
